  "body": "In test/e2e/empty_dir.go, we run a pod that basically runs once and logs status about the mounts, which we then validate.\n\nIn the test, we start the pod, wait for it to exit, and then get the logs.\n\nBut, we don't specify a restart policy.  The default is restart always.  So it will keep restarting.  So testContainerOutputInNamespace, which calls waitForPodSuccessInNamespace, will never exit: `ci.State.Termination` will be nil, though `ci.LastTerminationState.Termination` is getting set.\n\nI will propose a PR that sets RestartPolicy to never for the empty_dir test.  But there is a deeper issue - how did this test _ever_ pass?  How would it ever happen that State.Termination would be set, with RestartPolicy: Always?\n\n(I am hoping it is the other bug I found with kubelet restart, but I don't know that I entirely believe that)\n",
